FT  12 OCT 92 / Construction Contracts: Residences for Brunel students
NUGENT has been awarded contracts for both the public and private sectors
totalling Pounds 10m. These include a Pounds 5m design and build contract
for Brunel University to erect 400 student residences and a Pounds 2m
contract for Co-operative Retail Services for 50,000 sq ft of car showrooms
at Bedford.
Other contracts include major refurbishment works for the Victoria and
Albert Museum and Imperial College and a Pounds 1m contract for work at
Wormwood Scrubs prison
